<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="554" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d554">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Day</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Woodford</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-03-23"><hi rend="italic">March 23,
                                1898</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>The President approves your statement to the minister for the colonies,
                            as given in your No. 49. He will await your telegram after your
                            interview with the minister for foreign affairs.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Day.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>